    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-04T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-04T10:00:00-05:00" n="158"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d158">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20261/35: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-04T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 4, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 5, 11:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3794. Referring to your 1581, March 27th. I have seen the Swedish Foreign Office
                    in regard to Lomonossoff and they have cabled the Swedish Legation in Washington
                    instructions to grant him a vise to permit his entry into Sweden. …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MRS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
